headline: Smurfit Westrock (SW) Announces US$0.43 Dividend for September 2025 Payout
summary: Smurfit Westrock (SW) experienced a 17% price increase over the last quarter, amidst a capital restructuring through debt financing and the affirmation of a quarterly dividend of $0.43 per share. The company's removal from the Russell indexes could have countered the broader upward trend, yet overall market resilience, driven by robust earnings reports from major tech firms like Microsoft and Meta, likely supported investor confidence.
